2. "REQUEST_HEADERS|REQUEST_LINE" - This is a logical OR operator used to match either the request headers or the request line.
3. "^\(\s*\)\s+{" - This is the actual regular expression that matches the pattern. It starts with a caret (^) to indicate the beginning of the line, followed by a group of zero or more whitespace characters (\s*) enclosed in parentheses (\(\)), and then one or more whitespace characters (\s+) followed by an opening curly brace ({).

